                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, angular script</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS11077Zadengel">Za-Dǝngǝl</persName> is
                        mentioned as the scribe in Additio 1 and in supplication formulas, fols.
                        15va, 24ra. (probably the same scribe who wrote MR-040). <date from="1800" to="1850">First half of the 19th cent.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors;
                        incipit of <ref target="#ms_i1.1"/> and its subsections; incipit of
                        subsections of <ref target="#ms_i1.2"/>; the words mǝʿrāf, nagar and
                        taʾāmmǝr; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals; in the
                        incipit page of <ref target="#ms_i1"/>, two lines are rubricated,
                        alternating with black lines (s. <locus target="#3r"/>).</seg>
                     </handNote>

